code: import os import pandas as pd import torch from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader from torchvision import transforms, models from PIL import Image from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split from torch.cuda.amp import autocast, GradScaler import torch.nn.functional as F class CassavaDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, img_dir, transform=None, is_test=False): self.df = df self.img_dir = img_dir self.transform = transform self.is_test = is_test def __len__(self): return len(self.df) def __getitem__(self, idx): img_id = self.df.iloc[idx]["image_id"] img_path = os.path.join(self.img_dir, img_id) image = Image.open(img_path).convert("RGB") transformed = self.transform(image) return ( transformed if self.is_test else (transformed, self.df.iloc[idx]["label"]) ) # Hyperparameters IMG_SIZE = 384 BATCH_SIZE = 16 NUM_EPOCHS = 12 # Data preparation train_df = pd.read_csv("input/train.csv") train_df, val_df = train_test_split( train_df, test_size=0.1, stratify=train_df["label"], random_state=42 ) # Data transforms train_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.RandomResizedCrop(IMG_SIZE, scale=(0.6, 1.0)), transforms.RandAugment(num_ops=3, magnitude=12), transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(), transforms.RandomVerticalFlip(), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) val_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(IMG_SIZE + 64), transforms.CenterCrop(IMG_SIZE), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) # Dataset and loaders train_dataset = CassavaDataset(train_df, "input/train_images", train_transform) val_dataset = CassavaDataset(val_df, "input/train_images", val_transform) train_loader = DataLoader( train_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True ) val_loader = DataLoader( val_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True, ) # Model setup device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = models.convnext_large(weights=models.ConvNeXt_Large_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1) model.classifier[2] = torch.nn.Linear(model.classifier[2].in_features, 5) model = model.to(device) # Training config optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=5e-5, weight_decay=0.05) scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.CosineAnnealingLR( optimizer, T_max=NUM_EPOCHS, eta_min=1e-6 ) warmup_scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.LinearLR( optimizer, start_factor=0.01, total_iters=3 ) combined_scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.SequentialLR( optimizer, [warmup_scheduler, scheduler], milestones=[3] ) scaler = GradScaler() criterion = F.cross_entropy # Training loop best_val_acc = 0.0 for epoch in range(NUM_EPOCHS): model.train() for images, labels in train_loader: images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device) optimizer.zero_grad() with autocast(): outputs = model(images) loss = criterion(outputs, labels) scaler.scale(loss).backward() scaler.step(optimizer) scaler.update() combined_scheduler.step() # Validation model.eval() correct = 0 total = 0 with torch.no_grad(): for images, labels in val_loader: images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device) outputs = model(images) _, predicted = torch.max(outputs, 1) total += labels.size(0) correct += (predicted == labels).sum().item() val_acc = correct / total print( f"Epoch {epoch+1} Val Acc: {val_acc:.4f} | LR: {optimizer.param_groups[0]['lr']:.2e}" ) if val_acc > best_val_acc: best_val_acc = val_acc torch.save(model.state_dict(), "best_model.pth") print(f"Best Validation Accuracy: {best_val_acc:.4f}") # Inference model.load_state_dict(torch.load("best_model.pth")) model.eval() test_image_ids = [f for f in os.listdir("input/test_images") if f.endswith(".jpg")] test_df = pd.DataFrame({"image_id": test_image_ids}) test_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(IMG_SIZE + 64), transforms.CenterCrop(IMG_SIZE), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) test_dataset = CassavaDataset( test_df, "input/test_images", test_transform, is_test=True ) test_loader = DataLoader( test_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE * 2, shuffle=False, num_workers=8 ) predictions = [] with torch.no_grad(): for batch in test_loader: images = batch.to(device) outputs = model(images) outputs_h = model(torch.flip(images, [3])) outputs_v = model(torch.flip(images, [2])) avg_outputs = (outputs + outputs_h + outputs_v) / 3 predictions.extend(torch.argmax(avg_outputs, 1).cpu().numpy()) os.makedirs("submission", exist_ok=True) pd.DataFrame({"image_id": test_image_ids, "label": predictions}).to_csv( "submission/submission.csv", index=False ) print(f"Submission created. Final Val Accuracy: {best_val_acc:.4f}")
